></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>161</th><td class="r"><ins></ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>162</th><td class="r"><ins>Note that lighttpd doesn't support 'valid-user' in versions prior to 1.3.16.</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>163</th><td class="r"><ins></ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>164</th><td class="r"><ins>Conditional configuration is also useful for mapping static resources, i.e. serving out images and CSS directly instead of through FastCGI:</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>165</th><td class="r"><ins>{{{</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>166</th><td class="r"><ins># Aliasing functionality is needed</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>167</th><td class="r"><ins>server.modules += ("mod_alias")</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>168</th><td class="r"><ins></ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>169</th><td class="r"><ins># Setup an alias for the static resources</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>170</th><td class="r"><ins>alias.url = ("/trac/chrome/common" =&gt; "/usr/share/trac/htdocs")</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>171</th><td class="r"><ins></ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>172</th><td class="r"><ins># Use negative lookahead, matching all requests that ask for any resource under /trac, EXCEPT in</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>173</th><td class="r"><ins># /trac/chrome/common, and use FastCGI for those</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>174</th><td class="r"><ins>$HTTP["url"] =~ "^/trac(?!/chrome/common)" {</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>175</th><td class="r"><ins># Even if you have other fastcgi.server declarations for applications other than Trac, do NOT use += here</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>176</th><td class="r"><ins>fastcgi.server = ("/trac" =&gt;</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>177</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;("trac" =&gt;</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>178</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;("socket" =&gt; "/tmp/trac-fastcgi.sock",</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>179</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; "bin-path" =&gt; "/path/to/cgi-bin/trac.fcgi",</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>180</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; "check-local" =&gt; "disable",</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>181</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; "bin-environment" =&gt;</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>182</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ("TRAC_ENV" =&gt; "/path/to/projenv")</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>183</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;)</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>184</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;)</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>185</th><td class="r"><ins>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;)</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>186</th><td class="r"><ins>}</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>187</th><td class="r"><ins>}}}</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>188</th><td class="r"><ins>The technique can be easily adapted for use with multiple projects by creating aliases for each of them, and wrapping the fastcgi.server declarations inside conditional configuration blocks.</ins>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><th>&nbsp;</th><th>189</th><td class="r"><ins>Also there is another way to handle multiple projects and it's to use TRAC_ENV_PARENT_DIR instead of TRAC_ENV and use global auth, let's see an example:</ins>&n